      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "stream",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The stream to modify."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "streamEvents",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The set of events for which the client should receive callbacks. The events are listed in "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corefoundation/cfstreameventtype"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". If you pass "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corefoundation/cfstreameventtype/kcfstreameventnone"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", the current client for "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "stream"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " is removed."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "clientCB",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The client callback function to call when one of the events requested in "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "streamEvents"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " occurs. If "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "NULL"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", the current client for "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "stream"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " is removed."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "clientContext",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A structure holding contextual information for the stream client. The function copies the information out of the structure, so the memory pointed to by "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "clientContext"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " does not need to persist beyond the function call. If "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "NULL"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", the current client for "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "stream"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " is removed."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return_value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "true"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " if the stream supports asynchronous notification, "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "false"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " otherwise."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To avoid polling and blocking, you can register a client to hear about interesting events that occur on a stream. Only one client per stream is allowed; registering a new client replaces the previous one."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Once you have set a client, you need to schedule the stream in a run loop using "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corefoundation/1539621-cfwritestreamschedulewithrunloop"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " so that the client can receive the asynchronous notifications. You can schedule each stream in multiple run loops (for example, if you are using a thread pool). It is the caller's responsibility to ensure that at least one of the scheduled run loops is being run, otherwise the callback cannot be called."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Although all Core Foundation streams currently support asynchronous notification, future stream types may not. If a stream does not support asynchronous notification, this function returns "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "false"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". Typically, such streams never block for device I/O (for example, a stream writing to memory) and don’t benefit from asynchronous notification."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
